AirAsia, Malaysian Resources, Utusan: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-08-12T00:02:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/airasia-malaysian-resources-utusan-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 0.3 percent to
1,476.46.  Alam Maritim Resources Bhd. (AMRB)  : The oil and gas
marine services provider won contracts valued at 20.2 million
ringgit ($6.8 million) from Petronas Carigali Sdn. and a local
oil and gas company, according to an exchange filing. The shares
fell 0.7 percent to 76 sen.  AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA)  : The Employees Provident Fund,
Malaysia’s biggest pension fund, bought 12.3 million shares in
the budget carrier, an exchange filing showed. The fund bought
the shares on Aug. 5, according to the filing. The stock fell
1.1 percent to 3.50 ringgit.  KKB Engineering Bhd. (KKB)  : The engineering and
construction group won a 19.4 million-ringgit contract to supply
water pipes and pipe fittings to Kumpulan Bina Emas Sdn.,
according to a company statement. KKB lost 1.2 percent to 1.70
ringgit.  Malaysian Resources Corp. (MRC MK): The property and
construction group’s second-quarter net income rose 55 percent
from a year earlier to 19 million ringgit as sales increased,
according to a company statement. The shares climbed 1.4 percent
to 2.23 ringgit.       Utusan Melayu (Malaysia) Bhd. (UTUS MK): The Malaysian
newspaper publisher’s net loss in the second quarter narrowed to
473,000 ringgit from 5.07 million ringgit a year earlier,
according to a company statement. The shares gained 2.9 percent
to 71.5 sen on Aug. 10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
